timeline.message:
in swagger.json:
security:
apiKey: []
 
is incorrect.  Swagger validation throws error: Security requirements must match a security definition
 
Our security definition is as follows (see swagger.json line 1538: 
securityDefinitions:
access_token:
swagger.json should read:
security:
access_token: []
 
required changes in Java:
 
all annotations containing apiKey must be changes to access_token
Example:
@Api(value = "Patient", authorizations = @Authorization(value = "apiKey"))
should be changed to
@Api(value = "Patient", authorizations = @Authorization(value = "access_token"))
updated pom.xml to latest version of dropwizard
found a few more places where the auth method was wrong, previous commit eliminated errors
these annotations produce valid swagger outout for all resources except Endpoint which still has some swagger syntax errors on the parameters to create and update.
experimental config of maven swagger plugin

timeline.body:
Not sure if it was intentional, but if endpointID is a path param should it not remain with the @NotNull constraint?

This branch also seems to be failing due to the missing @NotNull on this particular operation, not including the annotation causes all the tests under EndpointResourceTest.java to fail. (Not sure why, maybe some sort of validation is causing this entire resource not to be loaded.)

```suggestion
    public Endpoint updateEndpoint(@ApiParam(value = "Your Organization's FHIR Endpoint ID") @NotNull @PathParam("endpointID") UUID endpointID,
```
timeline.bodyHTML:
Not sure if it was intentional, but if endpointID is a path param should it not remain with the @NotNull constraint?

This branch also seems to be failing due to the missing @NotNull on this particular operation, not including the annotation causes all the tests under EndpointResourceTest.java to fail. (Not sure why, maybe some sort of validation is causing this entire resource not to be loaded.)

Suggested change
public Endpoint updateEndpoint(@ApiParam(value = "Your Organization's FHIR Endpoint ID") @PathParam("endpointID") UUID endpointID,
public Endpoint updateEndpoint(@ApiParam(value = "Your Organization's FHIR Endpoint ID") @NotNull @PathParam("endpointID") UUID endpointID,
